      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>George Pegram was born 29 August 1755 in Dinwiddie County,
         Virginia. Pegram raised a company of volunteers during the
         American Revolution and served as its captain. He served in
         the House of Delegates representing Dinwiddie County from 1786
         to 1789. Pegram was a justice of the peace from 1788 to 1790.
         Pegram married Elizabeth Williamson and they had eight
         children.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Copy of land entry, 1 July 1800, for land in Dinwiddie
         County, Virginia, for George Pegram. Pegram presented land
         office treasury warrant no. 1, dated 14 November 1797, for the
         land. A second note, dated 8 March 1821, notes that the
         original was located the papers of the county clerk and that
         it was "mainly a probationary paper."</p>
      </scopecontent>
